# Tell GitHub's linguist to exclude embedded / vendored / test content
# from the repo's language-stats pie chart. None of these directories
# contain source code we *write* — they're URW fonts shipped with the
# binary, initialisation PS scripts, or ported test fixtures.
#
# The repo is a Rust project; the pie chart should say so.

# Workspace-root resources embedded via include_bytes! (35 URW fonts,
# init scripts, encodings, CMaps, ICC profile).
resources/**           linguist-vendored

# Per-crate copies of those resources — required for each crate tarball
# to be self-contained at publish time, but not "source" in any
# meaningful sense.
crates/stet/resources/**       linguist-vendored
crates/stet-pdf-reader/fonts/** linguist-vendored

# Embedded CMYK ICC profile (binary, not language content).
*.icc                  binary

# Unit-test PostScript programs — ported verbatim from the sister
# PostForge project; not language we maintain.
unit_tests/**          linguist-vendored

# Sample PS/EPS files kept for benchmarking and visual regression —
# data, not source.
ps_samples/**          linguist-vendored

# Vendored tiny-skia forks — upstream code with local modifications
# in a handful of files. Not ideal to mark wholly vendored, but for
# first-impression stats the Rust-we-actually-wrote is elsewhere.
crates/stet-tiny-skia/**       linguist-vendored
crates/stet-tiny-skia-path/**  linguist-vendored
